# Vim Motions
h, j, k, l       - move left, down, up, right
w, b             - move by word (forward/backward)
e, ge            - move to end of word (forward/backward)
0, ^, $          - move to start of line, first non-whitespace, end of line
gg, G            - go to top, bottom of file
<C-o>, <C-i>     - go to older, newer cursor position in jump list

# Editing
yy, dd, pp       - yank, delete, paste line
yi", di", ci"   - yank, delete, change inside quotes
ya", da", ca"   - yank, delete, change around quotes

# Visual Mode
v, V, <C-v>      - character, line, block visual mode
